rComments: While the content could be the foundation of a great course, the professor's all-encompassing dedication to active learning methods means that virtually no useful content is actually covered in class. Be ready to learn solely from the textbook, but you'll still need to guess on tests whether to use his 'answers' or the ones found in the textbook.
Haphazardly taught. Ineffective active learning measures, randomly patched together content, and a lot of unhappy students as a result.
Can't teach properly. Gives very hard tests focus on random stuffs that only appear once on the lecture slides. Expects you to read 100 pages of textbook before each lecture.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Test heavy']

rComments: Get ready to become real familiar with the textbook since he only teaches about 1/10th of the content during lecture. Oh, and he also puts tests the right on the day you get back from reading week. He killed any enthusiasm I had for biology before taking his course.
